.pages.navbar-through
  .page(data-page="transitions")
    .page-content
      .content-block-title Pages Animation
      .content-block
        .content-block-inner
          p One of the main target of Framework7 is to have native look and feel of iOS7 application. And Framework7 is the only framework that solves it and offers 1:1 animation of page changes with smooth parallax effect, changing opacity and shadow of newly loaded page.
      .content-block-title Swipe Back
      .content-block
        .content-block-inner
          p Framework7 supports iOS7 well known swipe back gesture from left border of screen if you want to get to the previous page. It works, just swipe from left (or drag with mouse) area of this page to see smooth transition to previous page.
      .content-block-title Dynamic Navbar
      .content-block
        .content-block-inner
          p As said above Framework7 does everything to gives you a feel of native iOS7 app. And on of significant features that will improve this feel is the dynamic top navbar. You can see like its elements sliding/fading during pages transition. Effect (slide/fade) for each element is easily configurable via additional classes.
      
      